System Logic Summary
The system's core computational loop is designed as an integrated, responsive architecture. It begins by establishing a TDEE hypothesis using predictive equations, which is immediately subjected to a feedback loop that recalibrates based on user weight trends (Sec 2.3). This validated TDEE is then partitioned into goal-oriented macronutrient targets based on the user's physiological state—anabolic or catabolic (Sec 3.0). These targets are then used by the meal generation algorithm to architect meals that prioritize satiety via volumetrics heuristics (Sec 4.2) and stabilize energy via Glycemic Load management (Sec 4.4). All recommendations operate under the foundational, non-negotiable constraints of the Acceptable Macronutrient Distribution Ranges (Sec 1.2) and the system's micronutrient risk-weighting algorithm (Sec 1.3), ensuring a safe, effective, and scientifically sound user experience.

